    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Genesis",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 17,
        "summary": "Abram is commanded to be perfect\u2014He will be a father of many nations\u2014His name is changed to Abraham\u2014The Lord covenants to be a God unto Abraham and his seed forever\u2014Also, the Lord gives Abraham the land of Canaan for an everlasting possession\u2014Circumcision becomes a token of the everlasting covenant between God and Abraham\u2014Sarai's name is changed to Sarah\u2014She will bear Isaac, with whom the Lord will establish His covenant\u2014Abraham and the men of his house are circumcised.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "And when Abram was ninety years old and nine, the Lord appeared to Abram, and said unto him, I am the Almighty God; walk before me, and be thou perfect.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Abr. 2:6 (6, 8, 19); 3:11.",
                        "start": 55,
                        "end": 63
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 6:3 (2\u20133).",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 72
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Power of; Jesus Christ, Power of.",
                        "start": 102,
                        "end": 114
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Walking with God.",
                        "start": 116,
                        "end": 120
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Integrity; Perfection.",
                        "start": 144,
                        "end": 151
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 95,
                        "end": 97
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And I will make my covenant between me and thee, and will multiply thee exceedingly.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Abrahamic Covenant.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 27
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Abram fell on his face: and God talked with him, saying,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Gen. 17:3\u201312 (Appendix).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "As for me, behold, my covenant is with thee, and thou shalt be a father of many nations.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 6:4.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 8:2; D&C 109:64; 132:49. TG\u00a0Seed of Abraham.",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 71
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Gen. 17:8\u20139 \u2026 nations. And this covenant I make, that thy children may be known among all nations \u2026 TG\u00a0Nations.",
                        "start": 80,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 33
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Neither shall thy name any more be called Abram, but thy name shall be Abraham; for a father of many nations have I made thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Chr. 1:27.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 78
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I will make thee exceeding fruitful, and I will make nations of thee, and kings shall come out of thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 26:22.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Israel, Blessings of.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 64
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Kings, Earthly.",
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 83
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I will establish my covenant between me and thee and thy seed after thee in their generations for an everlasting covenant, to be a God unto thee, and to thy seed after thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Gen. 17:11\u201312 (Appendix).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Israel, Mission of; New and Everlasting Covenant.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 29:14 (13\u201314).",
                        "start": 105,
                        "end": 125
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 24:12.",
                        "start": 135,
                        "end": 138
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And I will give unto thee, and to thy seed after thee, the land wherein thou art a stranger, all the land of Canaan, for an everlasting possession; and I will be their God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Gifts of.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Promised Lands.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 63
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Stranger.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 91
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Israel, Land of.",
                        "start": 101,
                        "end": 105
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 3:8 (1\u201310); Num. 34:2 (1\u201329); Abr. 2:19 (6, 19).",
                        "start": 109,
                        "end": 115
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 48:4; Abr. 2:6.",
                        "start": 136,
                        "end": 146
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 6:7.",
                        "start": 168,
                        "end": 171
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And God said unto Abraham, Thou shalt keep my covenant therefore, thou, and thy seed after thee in their generations.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "This is my covenant, which ye shall keep, between me and you and thy seed after thee; Every man child among you shall be circumcised.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Covenants.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Circumcision.",
                        "start": 121,
                        "end": 132
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 7
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And ye shall circumcise the flesh of your foreskin; and it shall be a token of the covenant betwixt me and you.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Acts 15:24; Moro. 8:8.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Signs.",
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 75
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "3\u00a0Ne. 20:12.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 91
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he that is eight days old shall be circumcised among you, every man child in your generations, he that is born in the house, or bought with money of any stranger, which is not of thy seed.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 84:28 (27\u201328).",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 12:44 (43\u201345).",
                        "start": 132,
                        "end": 138
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 173,
                        "end": 175
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that is born in thy house, and he that is bought with thy money, must needs be circumcised: and my covenant shall be in your flesh for an everlasting covenant.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "The covenant is everlasting, but circumcision as a sign of such a covenant was later discontinued. See Acts 15:1, 24\u201329; Gal. 2:3\u20134; 5:12\u201315.",
                        "start": 141,
                        "end": 161
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the uncircumcised man child whose flesh of his foreskin is not circumcised, that soul shall be cut off from his people; he hath broken my covenant.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 4:24.",
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 106
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And God said unto Abraham, As for Sarai thy wife, thou shalt not call her name Sarai, but Sarah shall her name be.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0Princess.",
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 101
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 111,
                        "end": 114
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And I will bless her, and give thee a son also of her: yea, I will bless her, and she shall be a mother of nations; kings of people shall be of her.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0God, Gifts of.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 30
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 95,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Then Abraham fell upon his face, and laughed, and said in his heart, Shall a child be born unto him that is an hundred years old? and shall Sarah, that is ninety years old, bear?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "JST\u00a0Gen. 17:23\u201324 (Appendix).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0(also) rejoiced. JST\u00a0Gen. 17:23 \u2026 rejoiced \u2026 TG\u00a0Laughter.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 44
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 21:5.",
                        "start": 111,
                        "end": 118
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 82
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And Abraham said unto God, O that Ishmael might live before thee!",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 21:11.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And God said, Sarah thy wife shall bear thee a son indeed; and thou shalt call his name Isaac: and I will establish my covenant with him for an everlasting covenant, and with his seed after him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 18:10 (10, 14); 21:1.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 19
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Seed of Abraham.",
                        "start": 119,
                        "end": 127
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 166,
                        "end": 169
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And as for Ishmael, I have heard thee: Behold, I have blessed him, and will make him fruitful, and will multiply him exceedingly; twelve princes shall he beget, and I will make him a great nation.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Seed of Abraham.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 25:16.",
                        "start": 130,
                        "end": 136
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But my covenant will I establish with Isaac, which Sarah shall bear unto thee at this set time in the next year.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Abrahamic Covenant.",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Gen. 21:2.",
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 24
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he left off talking with him, and God went up from Abraham.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Abraham took Ishmael his son, and all that were born in his house, and all that were bought with his money, every male among the men of Abraham's house; and circumcised the flesh of their foreskin in the selfsame day, as God had said unto him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Circumcision.",
                        "start": 161,
                        "end": 172
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And Abraham was ninety years old and nine, when he was circumcised in the flesh of his foreskin.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 12,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And Ishmael his son was thirteen years old, when he was circumcised in the flesh of his foreskin.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 23
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "In the selfsame day was Abraham circumcised, and Ishmael his son.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And all the men of his house, born in the house, and bought with money of the stranger, were circumcised with him.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}